House Resolution 176
By: Representative Smith of the 70th
A RESOLUTION
1 Honoring the life and memory of Johnese Threadcraft; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, the State of Georgia mourns the loss of one of its most distinguished citizens
3 with the passing of Johnese Threadcraft on November 18, 2024; and
4 WHEREAS, Johnese Threadcraft was born on June 12, 1951, in Calhoun County, Georgia,
5 a beloved daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Morris Lee Threadcraft Sr.; and
6 WHEREAS, she demonstrated remarkable courage in her early years by voluntarily
7 integrating Calhoun County High School before mandatory integration, excelling in her
8 studies and graduating with honors; and
9 WHEREAS, she continued her education at Georgia Southwestern College in Americus,
10 Georgia, where she again graduated with honors before embarking on a distinguished career
11 as an educator; and
12 WHEREAS, she began her professional career as an English and French teacher in Randolph
13 County and later continued her work in Atlanta at Henderson High School and Salem High
14 School in the DeKalb County School System; and
